# Styling and UI Guidelines

## Tailwind CSS

Always use valid Tailwind CSS classes for styling React and JSX pages:

```tsx
<div className="flex items-center justify-between p-4 bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md">
  <h2 className="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900">Title</h2>
  <button className="px-4 py-2 bg-blue-500 text-white rounded hover:bg-blue-600">
    Click Me
  </button>
</div>
```

## Icons

Request icons from **Nucleo** when needed. Do not use placeholder icon libraries.

## Block Kit (Slack UI)

For Slack interfaces, use Block Kit components:

```typescript
{
  type: 'section',
  text: {
    type: 'mrkdwn',
    text: '*Bold text* and _italic text_'
  }
}
```

## Best Practices

1. Use semantic HTML elements
2. Follow responsive design patterns with Tailwind breakpoints
3. Maintain consistent spacing and typography
4. Use Tailwind's color palette for consistency
5. Ensure accessibility with proper ARIA labels and semantic markup
